About Me

I am currently a senior at the Georgia Institute of Technology, studying Computer Science (B.S.) with concentrations in Artificial Intelligence, Networking, and Database Design, along with a certification in Finance. As a junior, I co-authored an original publication to the IEEE Systems Journal paper for the development of a novel systems engineering resilience metric and corresponding simulation software. In the summer of my sophomore year, I interned at John Deere Financial as a Data Analyst in the Customer Channel and Analytics team, developing their customer churn predictive model and streamlining it for production.
